                    <death when="0371" syriaca-computed-start="0371-01-01" source="#bib1173-1">371</death>
                    <state type="martyr" source="#bib1173-1">
                        <p>Martyr</p>
                    </state>
                    <note>Fiey provides the following bibliographic citations: <quote source="#bib1173-1">Manuscrit syriaque occidental, date de 1197, au Bnt1sh Museum (Catalogue Wnght,
1134- 35, cod. DCCCCLX, fol. 388r-394v n° 67) . Resume allemand Hoffmann,
Ausziige, 28- 33 ; BHO, 783.
Fiey, "Ma'In" , 437-53.
BSO, I, 419-20 (J.M. Fiey).</quote>
                    </note>
                    <note type="abstract" xml:id="abstract-en-1173">In hagiography: Benjamin was a hermit and
          priest from <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/67">Dara</placeName>; he was ordained
            by <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1161">Barsai of Edessa</persName> and
          travelled to <placeName ref="http://syriaca.org/place/524">Mount Sinjar</placeName>. He
            converted <persName ref="http://syriaca.org/person/1349">Maʿin</persName>; both Benjamin
          and Maʿin were martyred.</note>
                    <bibl xml:id="bib1173-1">
                        <title level="m" xml:lang="fr">Saints Syriaques</title>
                        <title level="a" xml:lang="fr">BENJAMIN</title>
